      "@type": "Project",
      "schema:legalName": "REPHY - REseau for the observation and monitoring of PHYtoplankton and hydrology in coastal waters",
      "schema:name": "REPHY - REseau for the observation and monitoring of PHYtoplankton and hydrology in coastal waters",
      "schema:url": "https://littoral.ifremer.fr/Reseaux-de-surveillance/Environnement/REPHY-la-surveillance-du-phytoplancton-et-des-phycotoxines",
      "schema:description": "REPHY is the main French observatory for marine phytoplankton. REPHY is part of a priority scientific axis of Ifremer by monitoring the dynamics of phytoplankton populations and the related hydrological conditions. Data on phytoplankton and the associated hydrological context, collected since 1987, contribute to a better scientific knowledge of the coastal marine environment through the study of the responses of phytoplankton communities to environmental changes (REPHY-Observation section), the assessment the quality of the coastal environment (REPHY-Surveillance section, in response to the WFD and the MSFD) and the impact of toxin-producing species (REPHY-Sanitary section).\r\nThe REPHY contributes to knowledge of the impact of climate change on marine biodiversity and participates in the monitoring of the ecological state of the marine environment for the Water Framework Directive (WFD) and the Marine Strategy Framework Directive (DCSMM). It is the main French observatory for marine phytoplankton. REPHY is part of a priority scientific axis of Ifremer by monitoring the dynamics of phytoplankton populations and the related hydrological conditions. This component is still under the supervision of Ifremer.",
